│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs due to an assertion in BoUpSLP::getVectorizedOperand expecting identical scalars in a TreeEntry, which isn't satisfied for this IR involving complex           │
│ PHI/uselistorder configurations during horizontal reduction handling. A minimal, safe fix is to replace the assert with a defensive check that returns nullptr when scalars mismatch,    │
│ and then make getSpillCost resilient to nullptr by skipping spill cost computation for such operands. This avoids aborting and lets the vectorizer conservatively bail out on            │
│ problematic patterns. I'll patch SLPVectorizer.cpp accordingly and submit the patch.                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
